Education systems. Organisation of education and education policy. Nature and general principles of law. Hierarchy and structure of legal acts. Legislative drafting and main legal acts concerning the right to education. Institutional development activities in the field of education.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To develop skills to orientate oneself in the organisation of education and education policy and relevant legal acts both on the institutional and national levels. To develop skills to interpret and use legal acts. To give the students readiness to develop the activities of an institution of education.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has completed the course:  - understands the principles of education policy and organisation of education, and orientate themselves in the Estonian organisation of education; - is able to compare and analyse the organisation of education and the main trends of education policy in Estonia as well as other countries;  - orientate themselves in the legal acts regulating the field of education and is able to prepare motions to amend; - is able to analyse the reasons for problems in Estonian education and develop potential solutions, using the sources of information that handle the right to education, education policy and organisation of education.
